{"title":"Favero Assioma DUO-Shi puts power meters inside your Shimano SPD-SL road pedals","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/23/favero-assioma-duo-shi-puts-power-meters-inside-your-shimano-spd-sl-road-pedals/","date":1627052969000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Two years ago we turned up the Favero Assioma, the lightest power meter pedals you’ve never heard of, but now they are back with a new set of DUO-Shi spindles that slide power measurement into your existing Shimano road pedal bodies. Why is that better than their original <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/05/15/favero-assioma-the-lightest-road-pedal-power-meter-youve-never-heard-of/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Look-compatible version</a>? And what are the downsides? Let me explain…</p><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x242/rscb26/ng:webp/ngcb26\" alt=\"Favero Assioma power meter pedals, lightest two-sided left/right low maintenance pedal-based powermeter\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors-120x60.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors-297x149.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors-768x384.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors-696x348.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 696w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x242/rscb26/ng:webp/ngcb26\" ezoid=\"0.42533285458507253\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors-120x60.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors-297x149.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors-768x384.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_internal-sensors-696x348.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 696w\"></a></p><p>Favero’s Assioma power meter pedals are simple in concept. With the strain gauges inside a special set of spindles and the electronics for power, processing &amp; communication inside a compact housing around the stainless steel axle next to your crank arm, they are compact &amp; self-contained. That means a lightweight, conventional road pedal body that works with regular road cleats (&amp; road shoes), and all the sensitive gadget bits are safely out of the way of regular road impacts &amp; possible crash damage.</p><p>And as with most pedal-based power meters, they are quick &amp; easy to move from one bike to the next.</p><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded.jpg\" alt=\"Favero Assioma power meter pedals, lightest two-sided left/right low maintenance pedal-based powermeter\" width=\"800\" height=\"500\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-120x75.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-297x186.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-768x480.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-696x435.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-672x420.jpg 672w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-120x75.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-297x186.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-768x480.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-696x435.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Favero-Assioma-power-meter-pedals_lightest-two-sided-left-right-low-maintenance-pedal-based-powermeter_exploded-672x420.jpg 672w\"></a></p><p>The fact that the Look-compatible Assioma pedals deliver top-tier ±1% power accuracy at just 150g per pedal, low 10.5mm stack, low 54mm pedal Q-factor, at just 690€ for true dual-sided power measurement is hard to argue with.</p><p>But…</p><p>A lot of road cyclists are super picky about their pedals. And many prefer the wider pedal platform support of Shimano SPD-SL pedals, even their improved walkability. So Favero has been developing a Shimano-compatible Assioma DUO system for quite some time. And now it’s ready.</p><h3>What’s new in DUO-Shi? And why?</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup.jpg\" alt=\"Favero Assioma DUO-Shi Shimano SPD-SL compatible road power meter pedal spindle kit, render\" width=\"1200\" height=\"700\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-297x173.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-800x467.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-768x448.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-696x406.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-1068x623.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-720x420.jpg 720w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-297x173.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-800x467.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-768x448.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-696x406.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-1068x623.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175712/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_mockup-720x420.jpg 720w\"></a></p><p>Basically, Favero reworked their Assioma power metering spindle to fit inside the regular Shimano pedal bodies that you are already riding. It’s actually cheaper than their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/05/15/favero-assioma-the-lightest-road-pedal-power-meter-youve-never-heard-of/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Look DUO</a> setup, and you can upgrade Shimano SPD-SL pedals from Tiagra all the way up to Ultegra with the same DUO-Shi setup.</p><p>The catch?</p><p>Your pedal stance is going to get a lot wider – your feet are going to end up around 2cm farther apart…</p><h3>Wider pedal Q-factor</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor.jpg\" alt=\"Favero Assioma DUO-Shi Shimano SPD-SL compatible road power meter pedal spindle kit, Q-facto &amp; stack heightr \" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-297x149.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-800x400.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-768x384.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-696x348.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-1068x534.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-840x420.jpg 840w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-297x149.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-800x400.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-768x384.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-696x348.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-1068x534.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175718/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_stack-height_Q-factor-840x420.jpg 840w\"></a></p><p>The 64-65mm DUO-Shi pedal Q-factor (<em>add that to crank arm Q-factor to see how wide your feet will be from the centerline of the bike</em>) adds 12.8mm to each side over the standard 52mm Q-factor Ultegra pedal, or 8.8mm extra if you have Shimano’s extended axle <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/29/shimano-goes-long-w-dura-ace-ultegra-axle-options-for-those-who-need-wider-stance/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ergonomic 56mm Q</a> pedal spindles. Double that to see how much further apart your feet will be.</p><p>Now is that a problem?</p><p>Many road cyclists have found ergonomic improvement from going to wider pedals to balance wider thighs or hips, but that won’t be everybody. Most road pedals are in that 52-56mm Q of Ultegra pedals, but Speedplay were often praised for originally offering up to a 65mm Q-factor spindle.</p><p>And even some cyclists who ride more on mountain bikes (which generally have much wider cranks Q-factor to fit bigger tires) have favored increased Q on their road or gravel bikes for a similar ride. Then again, many (<em>like myself</em>) often jump from super-low road/gravel bike Q (52mm pedals on 145.5mm cranks) to much wider MTB trail bike Q (57mm pedals on 172mm cranks) without any issue – that’s more than 3cm per side!</p><p>Whether the extra Q-factor of the Assioma DUO-Shi power meter pedals will be a problem is going to be a personal decision. But Favero figures many riders will still benefit from the upgrade to power metering.</p><h3>Tech details</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details.jpg\" alt=\"Favero Assioma DUO-Shi Shimano SPD-SL compatible road power meter pedal spindle kit, angled\" width=\"1723\" height=\"1149\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details.jpg 1723w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1723px) 100vw, 1723px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details.jpg 1723w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175706/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit_angled-details-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The bulk of the tech &amp; spindle is the same as in the original Favero Assioma, inside a new adapter for the Shimano pedal body, although not interchangeable or able to be converted from the Look version.</p><p>That means you get the same ANT+ &amp; BLE transmission of data with L/R balance, torque effectiveness, pedal smoothness, IAV Power Phase, and IAV Rider Position. The power meters are rated up to 3000W with +/-1% accuracy. They feature built-in cadence sensors, 50hr lithium batteries rechargeable with Favero’s USB dongle.</p><p>What is different is that the Assioma DUO-Shi uses a tiny sealed bearing at the outside (like the original Assioma), but a low-friction glide bushing on the inside due to space constraints in the Shimano bodies.</p><p>Each sensor spindle weighs 99g without a pedal body, meaning a claimed weight of 157g per pedal with an Ultegra R8000 pedal body installed (just over 33g more than <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2017/06/07/shimano-ultegra-r8000-picks-mechanical-di2-disc-brake-dura-ace-tech/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Shimano’s claimed weight</a> per pedal.)</p><h3>How To get dual-sided power metering from Shimano pedals?</h3><p><span><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/oKwmfLNwsMM?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><p>OK, so now that we understand the tech inside (and you are fine with the added Q-factor), you still can only buy the spindles themselves. You still have to install them into your existing Shimano SPD-SL pedal bodies yourself. It’s not such a difficult process, and Favero had the step-by-step instructions to get you there.</p><h3>Favero Assioma DUO-Shi power meters – Pricing &amp; compatibility</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Favero Assioma DUO-Shi Shimano SPD-SL compatible road power meter pedal spindle kit\" width=\"1600\" height=\"450\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail-297x84.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail-800x225.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail-120x34.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail-768x216.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail-1536x432.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail-696x196.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22175701/Favero-Assioma-DUO-Shi-Shimano-SPD-SL-compatible-road-power-meter-pedal-spindle-kit-detail-1068x300.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ez